{"id":713,"date":"2022-04-04T16:05:00","date_gmt":"2022-04-04T13:05:00","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/?p=713"},"modified":"2022-03-23T21:50:38","modified_gmt":"2022-03-23T19:50:38","slug":"digital-banking-explained-all-you-need-to-know","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/digital-banking-explained-all-you-need-to-know\/","title":{"rendered":"Digital Banking Explained: Checking Accounts, Savings Accounts, And More!"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Digital banking gives you the ability to access everyday banking tasks via a mobile phone or computer and the capacity to enable cashless transactions at a wide range of establishments. Through banking as a service, you can acquire a digital banking account such as checking accounts, savings accounts, business accounts, and investment accounts.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The phrase &#8220;digital banking&#8221; involves developing banking services. It also delivers products over electronic means such as ATMs, telephones, the internet, and cellular phones. In the recent past, reports show that <a href=\"https:\/\/thefintechtimes.com\/report-finds-total-global-investment-in-digital-banks-topped-3-7billion-in-q1-2021\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">investment in digital banking<\/a> is on the rise.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Due to the rise of digital banking services, <a href=\"https:\/\/techcrunch.com\/2022\/02\/08\/american-express-launches-its-first-all-digital-consumer-checking-account\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">traditional banks<\/a> are enhancing their digital strategies and offering more competitive banking offers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Below is an extensive review of all digital accounts offered by various banks. It includes <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/online-banking-made-easier-with-online-banking\/#:~:text=Here%20are%20some%20of%20the%20key%20banking%20features%20that%20you%20should%20enjoy%20when%20signing%20up%20for%20banking%20online%20to%20make%20digital%20payments\">features<\/a>, pros, and cons of these accounts to help the reader make an informed choice.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_45 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-grey ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<div class=\"ez-toc-title-container\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Table of Contents<\/p>\n<span class=\"ez-toc-title-toggle\"><a href=\"#\" class=\"ez-toc-pull-right ez-toc-btn ez-toc-btn-xs ez-toc-btn-default ez-toc-toggle\" area-label=\"ez-toc-toggle-icon-1\"><label for=\"item-673d6642b02e3\" aria-label=\"Table of Content\"><span style=\"display: flex;align-items: center;width: 35px;height: 30px;justify-content: center;direction:ltr;\"><svg style=\"fill: #999;color:#999\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" class=\"list-377408\" width=\"20px\" height=\"20px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M6 6H4v2h2V6zm14 0H8v2h12V6zM4 11h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2zM4 16h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2z\" fill=\"currentColor\"><\/path><\/svg><svg style=\"fill: #999;color:#999\" class=\"arrow-unsorted-368013\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" width=\"10px\" height=\"10px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" version=\"1.2\" baseProfile=\"tiny\"><path d=\"M18.2 9.3l-6.2-6.3-6.2 6.3c-.2.2-.3.4-.3.7s.1.5.3.7c.2.2.4.3.7.3h11c.3 0 .5-.1.7-.3.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7zM5.8 14.7l6.2 6.3 6.2-6.3c.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7c-.2-.2-.4-.3-.7-.3h-11c-.3 0-.5.1-.7.3-.2.2-.3.5-.3.7s.1.5.3.7z\"\/><\/svg><\/span><\/label><input  type=\"checkbox\" id=\"item-673d6642b02e3\"><\/a><\/span><\/div>\n<nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/digital-banking-explained-all-you-need-to-know\/#digital-banking-all-about-checking-accounts\" title=\"Digital Banking: All About Checking Accounts\">Digital Banking: All About Checking Accounts<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3'><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/digital-banking-explained-all-you-need-to-know\/#the-advantages-of-checking-accounts-on-digital-banking\" title=\"The Advantages of Checking Accounts on Digital Banking\">The Advantages of Checking Accounts on Digital Banking<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/digital-banking-explained-all-you-need-to-know\/#disadvantages-of-checking-accounts\" title=\"Disadvantages of Checking Accounts\">Disadvantages of Checking Accounts<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/digital-banking-explained-all-you-need-to-know\/#a-review-of-savings-accounts\" title=\"A Review of Savings Accounts\">A Review of Savings Accounts<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3'><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/digital-banking-explained-all-you-need-to-know\/#the-advantages-of-saving-accounts\" title=\"The Advantages of Saving Accounts\">The Advantages of Saving Accounts<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/digital-banking-explained-all-you-need-to-know\/#the-disadvantages-of-saving-accounts\" title=\"The Disadvantages of Saving Accounts\">The Disadvantages of Saving Accounts<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/digital-banking-explained-all-you-need-to-know\/#all-about-business-accounts\" title=\"All About Business Accounts\">All About Business Accounts<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3'><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-8\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/digital-banking-explained-all-you-need-to-know\/#the-advantages-of-business-accounts\" title=\"The Advantages of Business Accounts\">The Advantages of Business Accounts<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-9\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/digital-banking-explained-all-you-need-to-know\/#the-disadvantages-of-business-accounts\" title=\"The Disadvantages of Business Accounts\">The Disadvantages of Business Accounts<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-10\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/digital-banking-explained-all-you-need-to-know\/#everything-you-need-to-know-about-investment-accounts\" title=\"Everything you Need to know about Investment Accounts\">Everything you Need to know about Investment Accounts<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3'><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-11\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/digital-banking-explained-all-you-need-to-know\/#advantages-of-investment-accounts\" title=\"Advantages of Investment Accounts\">Advantages of Investment Accounts<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-12\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/digital-banking-explained-all-you-need-to-know\/#disadvantages-of-investment-accounts\" title=\"Disadvantages of Investment Accounts\">Disadvantages of Investment Accounts<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-13\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/digital-banking-explained-all-you-need-to-know\/#which-is-the-best-account-for-you\" title=\"Which is the Best Account for You?\">Which is the Best Account for You?<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"digital-banking-all-about-checking-accounts\"><\/span>Digital Banking: All About Checking Accounts<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Checking accounts are bank accounts used for daily cash deposits and withdrawals. You can deposit money into a checking account, which later can make payments.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can deposit your paycheck into your checking account and use it to pay most of your bills every pay cycle. Checking accounts are referred to as <a href=\"https:\/\/www.forbes.com\/advisor\/banking\/what-is-a-checking-account\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">&#8220;transactional accounts&#8221;<\/a> since they don&#8217;t have a restriction on how many transactions you can make or levy fees for excess transactions.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, don&#8217;t just take the account name at face value and think it&#8217;s the perfect one for you without doing some research.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"the-advantages-of-checking-accounts-on-digital-banking\"><\/span>The Advantages of Checking Accounts on Digital Banking<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>There&#8217;s always a record of your expenditure: Banks track your spending, even if you solely make checks on your account. It could be a carbon copy of a review, an electronic or physical statement from the bank, or check documents already paid out by the bank, making creating an individual budget and managing expenditures a lot easier.<\/li><li>Accessibility of your money: A checking account&#8217;s goal is to simplify the accessibility of your funds. They use a blend of cheques, debit cards, and internet payment alternatives.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>When shopping, all you have to do is swipe your debit card or write a check from your checking account to pay for your purchases. There is no need for cash. If you need to make a cash payment, you can use your card to withdraw money from an ATM.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Fees on online checking accounts are lower: Another advantage of online checking accounts is the low fees, which result from lower overhead costs passed on to the customer. Because online banks often do not have specialized ATMs, they usually refund their customers for out-of-network withdrawal fees.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"disadvantages-of-checking-accounts\"><\/span>Disadvantages of Checking Accounts<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>There are a few disadvantages to online checking accounts, including the lack of face-to-face client support. Sitting down with a personal banker at your local branch can help you deal with any account concerns that arise. The best you can hope for is a call centre representative at a toll-free customer service number. Some online banks provide phone customer support 24 hours, while others confine it to typical business hours.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"a-review-of-savings-accounts\"><\/span>A Review of Savings Accounts<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A savings account is a bank account that allows you to keep your money safe while accruing compound interest.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you need somewhere to keep your money that you&#8217;ll utilize to pay bills or cover expenses, a checking account is an ultimate option. On the other hand, a savings account may be a superior option for putting money aside for future needs and objectives.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"the-advantages-of-saving-accounts\"><\/span>The Advantages of Saving Accounts<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Improved monthly savings: Some banks require a minimum balance for sustainability. If the account holder fails to do so, charging fees will apply. There are no monthly maintenance fees, and the interest rate is competitive.<\/li><li>You earn interest on savings: The money in your <a href=\"https:\/\/www.forbes.com\/advisor\/banking\/what-is-a-savings-account\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">savings account will earn interest<\/a> from the bank. It&#8217;s a fantastic bonus (benefit) though the interest rates are subject to market fluctuations.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Savings accounts allow you to grow your money without putting in any extra effort. Although this isn&#8217;t free money (interest earnings must be taxed), it is money you can make passively by saving regularly.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Free transfers: You can make unlimited free transfers such as NEFT, RTGS, and card payments with a digital savings account.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"the-disadvantages-of-saving-accounts\"><\/span>The Disadvantages of Saving Accounts<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Saving accounts have less personalization: If you have an online-only savings account, you won&#8217;t be able to make your way to the bank teller to ask a question, make a deposit or get help with your account.<\/li><li>It is cumbersome to make deposits: It&#8217;s simple to deposit a check into your online savings account by taking a photo of it with your bank&#8217;s app. On the other hand, depositing cash requires either finding an ATM that accepts cash deposits or getting a friend cash a check on your behalf.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"400\" src=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/business-account-digital-banking.jpg\" alt=\"business accounts in digital banking\" class=\"wp-image-766\" srcset=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/business-account-digital-banking.jpg 800w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/business-account-digital-banking-300x150.jpg 300w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/business-account-digital-banking-768x384.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"all-about-business-accounts\"><\/span>All About Business Accounts<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A business bank account keeps you protected and complying with the law. It also has merits for your clients and workers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Business accounts allow you to keep track of your cash flows and keep them distinct from your finances. It takes more work to open a company bank account than a personal one.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"the-advantages-of-business-accounts\"><\/span>The Advantages of Business Accounts<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Accessibility of credit for your business: A line of credit for the corporation in business banking can be used in an emergency or if your company requires new equipment.<\/li><li>Professionalism in customer handling: Clients will be able to pay you with checks or credit cards payable to your enterprise rather than directly to you. You&#8217;ll also be able to delegate day-to-day banking chores to staff on behalf of the company.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"the-disadvantages-of-business-accounts\"><\/span>The Disadvantages of Business Accounts<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>The same FDIC insurance limitations apply to business checking accounts to personal accounts.<\/li><li>Numerous fees are only applicable to business accounts, not personal checking accounts. A well-established firm, for example, is generally required to maintain a relatively high minimum balance and may be charged fees if it fails to do so.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"everything-you-need-to-know-about-investment-accounts\"><\/span>Everything you Need to know about Investment Accounts<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The main goal of an investing account is to earn a higher rate of return than other options, such as a bank savings account. Investment banking is a branch of banking specializing in assisting individuals and businesses in raising funds and providing financial advice.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Banks link security issuers and investors and assist new businesses in going public.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"advantages-of-investment-accounts\"><\/span>Advantages of Investment Accounts<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Investment accounts offer the possibility of high investment returns.<\/li><li>A personal investment account helps determine how to invest your money in the fund. Investing depends on your risk tolerance and investment criteria. You control your portfolio&#8217;s fate.<\/li><li>It is possible to make a long-term investment.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"disadvantages-of-investment-accounts\"><\/span>Disadvantages of Investment Accounts<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Returns on a personal investment account are not guaranteed.<\/li><li>There is the risk of capital loss.<\/li><li>Depending on the type of account you open, long-term investments will ban you from making early withdrawals.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"which-is-the-best-account-for-you\"><\/span>Which is the Best Account for You?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Digital banking is no longer a prospect. It is happening now. <a href=\"https:\/\/australianfintech.com.au\/new-technologies-key-driver-of-digital-banking\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">New technologies<\/a> are the driving forces behind digital banking, and If you need a checking account, business account, savings account, or investment account, you can access them digitally. The type of account you need solely depends on the purpose you intend to use it with. Choose one of the many digital accounts and stand to benefit.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Learn about digital banking and Checking, Savings, Business, and Investment accounts. Safeguard your money with the correct banking account.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":764,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"close